#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:31
msgid ""
"The procedure for installing fonts on Rocky Linux is to save the fonts you "
"want to add somewhere, and then install them with the `fc-cache` command. "
"This procedure is not a true installation so much as a registration of the "
"new fonts in the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:33
msgid "!!! warning \"Creation of compressed packages\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "\tThe procedure described below is not a standard procedure as each developer has packaged fonts using a custom scheme. So once downloaded and extracted, the contents must be checked to choose the procedure for copying the fonts.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:37
msgid "For this guide we will use the `Sauce Code Pro Nerd` font."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:39
msgid "Download the package with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts/releases/download/v2.3.3/SourceCodePro.zip\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:45
msgid ""
"Next, unzip the contents of the folder and copy the fonts to `~/.local/share/"
"fonts/` with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nerd_fonts.md:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mkdir ~/.local/share/fonts\n"
"unzip SourceCodePro.zip -d ~/.local/share/fonts/\n"
"fc-cache ~/.local/share/fonts\n"
msgstr ""

